    <h1>Easy Butter Chicken Recipe</h1>
    <p>Looking to create a simple, flavour packed butter chicken? Then you've come to the right place. No complicated ingredients or skill needed, just one pot and 25 minutes!</p>
    <img src="https://feelgoodfoodie.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Easy-Butter-Chicken-TIMG.jpg" alt="Butter Chicken" height="300">
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>250g Chicken Breast</li>
      <li>3 Tablespoons Greek Yogurt</li>
      <li>2 Tablespoons Coconut Oil</li>
      <li>Cumin</li>
      <li>Paprika</li>
      <li>Tumeric</li>
      <li>Chilli Powder</li>
      <li>2 Garlic Cloves, crushed</li>
      <li>Ginger powder</li>
      <li>4 Tomatoes</li>
      <li>1 Onion0</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Instructions</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Cut the chicken breast into cubes and marinade in the greek yogurt mixed with the spices for 10 mins.</li>
      <li>Pre-heat the coconut oil in a pan.</li>
      <li>Blend the onion, garlic cloves and tomatoes into a fine paste.</li>
      <li>Fry the chicken until golden brown, then add in the blended mix and let simmer until fully cooked. Enjoy with a side of rice and naan!</li>
    </ol>
